@startuml
title Stays4Pilgrims - Project Architecture Overview

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor User

component "Frontend\n(Web / Mobile)" as FE

package "Backend (NestJS)" as BE {
  component "Auth + Accounts" as AUTH
  component "Places / Accommodations" as ACC
  component "Caminos / Stages / Statistics" as ROUTES
  component "Comments / Favorites / Suggestions" as SOCIAL
  component "Upload" as UPLOAD
  component "Content Moderation" as MOD
}

database "PostgreSQL\n(managed / Supabase)" as DB
cloud "Cloudinary" as CLOUDINARY
cloud "Email provider\n(Resend or SMTP)" as EMAIL
cloud "OpenAI\n(optional moderation)" as OPENAI

User --> FE : browse / submit content
FE --> BE : HTTPS REST API

AUTH --> DB : users, sessions, tokens
ACC --> DB : places, categories, requests
ROUTES --> DB : caminos, stages, statistics
SOCIAL --> DB : comments, favorites
UPLOAD --> CLOUDINARY : upload / delete media
UPLOAD --> MOD : pre-check and post-check
MOD --> OPENAI : optional image/comment moderation
AUTH --> EMAIL : verification / reset / welcome emails
BE --> DB : TypeORM / SQL

note right of BE
  Main modules registered in AppModule:
  - AuthModule
  - AccountsModule
  - AccommodationsModule
  - CaminosModule
  - StagesModule
  - StatisticsCaminosModule
  - FavoritesModule
  - CommentsModule
  - UploadModule
  - ContentModerationModule
end note

note bottom of FE
  Frontend is the client for all user interactions.
  It consumes the NestJS API and renders the UI.
end note

@enduml